A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Health Maintenance Organizations – Payments to Nonparticipating Providers –
3 Reimbursement Rate
4 FOR the purpose of altering the reimbursement rate at which health maintenance
5 organizations are required to pay certain nonparticipating health care providers for
6 services; and generally relating to payments by health maintenance organizations to
7 nonparticipating providers.
8 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
9 Article – Health – General
10 Section 19–710.1
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
