4 (b) In addition to any other provisions of this subtitle, for a covered service
5 rendered to an enrollee of a health maintenance organization by a health care provider not
6 under written contract with the health maintenance organization, the health maintenance
7 organization or its agent:
8 (1) Shall pay the health care provider within 30 days after the receipt of a
9 claim in accordance with the applicable provisions of this subtitle; and
10 (2) Shall pay the claim submitted by:
11 (i) A hospital at the rate approved by the Health Services Cost
12 Review Commission;
13 (ii) A trauma physician for trauma care rendered to a trauma
14 patient in a trauma center, at the greater of:
15 1. 140% of the rate paid by the Medicare program, as
16 published by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services, for the same covered service,
17 to a similarly licensed provider; or
18 2. The rate as of January 1, 2001 that the health
19 maintenance organization paid in the same geographic area, as published by the Centers
20 for Medicare and Medicaid Services, for the same covered service, to a similarly licensed
21 provider; and
22 (iii) Any other health care provider:
23 1. For an evaluation and management service, no less than
24 the greater of:
25 A. 125% of the average rate the health maintenance
26 organization paid as of [January 1 of the previous calendar year] JANUARY 31, 2019, in
27 the same geographic area, as defined by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services,
28 for the same covered service, to similarly licensed providers under written contract with
29 the health maintenance organization, INFLATED BY THE CHANGE IN THE MEDICARE
30 ECONOMIC INDEX FROM 2019 TO THE CURRENT YEAR; or
31 B. 140% of the rate paid by Medicare, as published by the
32 Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services, for the same covered service to a similarly
33 licensed provider in the same geographic area as of August 1, 2008, inflated by the change
34 in the Medicare Economic Index from 2008 to the current year; and

