1 2. For a service that is not an evaluation and management
2 service, no less than 125% of the average rate the health maintenance organization paid as
3 of [January 1 of the previous calendar year] JANUARY 31, 2019, in the same geographic
4 area, as defined by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services, to a similarly licensed
5 provider under written contract with the health maintenance organization for the same
6 covered service, INFLATED BY THE CHANGE IN THE MEDICARE ECONOMIC INDEX
7 FROM 2019 TO THE CURRENT YEAR.
8 (c) For the purposes of subsection (b)(2)(iii) of this section, a health maintenance
9 organization shall calculate the average rate paid to similarly licensed providers under
10 written contract with the health maintenance organization for the same covered service by
11 summing the contracted rate for all occurrences of the Current Procedural Terminology
12 Code for that service and then dividing by the total number of occurrences of the Current
13 Procedural Terminology Code.
14 (d) A health maintenance organization shall disclose, on request of a health care
15 provider not under written contract with the health maintenance organization, the
16 reimbursement rate required under subsection (b)(2)(ii) and (iii) of this section.
17 (e) (1) Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, a health maintenance
18 organization may require a trauma physician not under contract with the health
19 maintenance organization to submit appropriate adjunct claims documentation and to
20 include on the uniform claim form a provider number assigned to the trauma physician by
21 the health maintenance organization.
22 (2) If a health maintenance organization requires a trauma physician to
23 include a provider number on the uniform claim form in accordance with paragraph (1) of
24 this subsection, the health maintenance organization shall assign a provider number to a
25 trauma physician not under contract with the health maintenance organization at the
26 request of the physician.
27 (3) A trauma center, on request from a health maintenance organization,
28 shall verify that a licensed physician is credentialed or otherwise designated by the trauma
29 center to provide trauma care.
30 (4) Notwithstanding the provisions of § 19–701(d) of this subtitle, for
31 trauma care rendered to a trauma patient in a trauma center by a trauma physician, a
32 health maintenance organization may not require a referral or preauthorization for a
33 service to be covered.
34 (f) (1) A health maintenance organization may seek reimbursement from an
35 enrollee for any payment under subsection (b) of this section for a claim or portion of a claim
36 submitted by a health care provider and paid by the health maintenance organization that
37 the health maintenance organization determines is the responsibility of the enrollee.

