1 (2) The health maintenance organization may request and the health care
2 provider shall provide adjunct claims documentation to assist in making the determination
3 under paragraph (1) of this subsection or under subsection (b) of this section.
4 (g) (1) A health care provider may enforce the provisions of this section by
5 filing a complaint against a health maintenance organization with the Maryland Insurance
6 Administration or by filing a civil action in a court of competent jurisdiction under § 1–501
7 or § 4–201 of the Courts Article.
8 (2) The Maryland Insurance Administration or a court shall award
9 reasonable attorney fees if the complaint of the health care provider is sustained.
10 (h) The Maryland Health Care Commission annually shall review payments to
11 health care providers to determine the compliance of health maintenance organizations
12 with the requirements of this section and report its findings to the Maryland Insurance
13 Administration.
14 (i) The Maryland Insurance Administration may take any action authorized
15 under this subtitle or the Insurance Article, including conducting an examination under
16 Title 2, Subtitle 2 of the Insurance Article, to investigate and enforce a violation of the
17 provisions of this section.
18 (j) In addition to any other penalties under this subtitle, the Commissioner may
19 impose a penalty not to exceed $5,000 on any health maintenance organization which
20 violates the provisions of this section if the violation is committed with such frequency as
21 to indicate a general business practice of the health maintenance organization.
22 (k) The Maryland Insurance Administration, in consultation with the Maryland
23 Health Care Commission, shall adopt regulations to implement this section.
24 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
25 October 1, 2025.

